WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.735 --> 00:00:04.067
<i>Previously on</i> Elementary:

2
00:00:04.237 --> 00:00:08.970
- Hannah. the guy laid hands on you.
- I am not 9 years old anymore. Dad.

3
00:00:09.909 --> 00:00:11.399
I wanna be promoted just as bad
as the next cop.

4
00:00:11.578 --> 00:00:13.739
and I'm not just talking
about detective.

5
00:00:13.913 --> 00:00:16.643
I want to be captain someday.
like you.

6
00:00:17.584 --> 00:00:21.418
But it's never gonna happen if people
look at me and they see "victim."

7
00:00:24.791 --> 00:00:26.281
<i>Watson. you still over there?</i>

8
00:00:26.459 --> 00:00:29.326
Yes. I'm still here because
I can't go home because of you.

9
00:00:29.496 --> 00:00:31.396
Why did you bring the bees
in the house anyway?

10
00:00:31.564 --> 00:00:33.828
Varroa mites are a pernicious threat
to the colony.

11
00:00:34.000 --> 00:00:36.491
I intended a thorough inspection.
as well as an application

12
00:00:36.669 --> 00:00:38.830
of baker's sugar
as a preventative measure.

13
00:00:39.005 --> 00:00:40.996
My thoughts were concerned
with colony collapse.

14
00:00:41.174 --> 00:00:44.143
<i>I failed to see the more urgent
threat of table collapse.</i>

15
00:00:44.310 --> 00:00:47.711
Wait a second. You're not talking
about my table. are you?

16
00:00:47.881 --> 00:00:49.246
<i>The one I bought
for my apartment?</i>

17
00:00:49.416 --> 00:00:51.884
Two hours should be sufficient
to return the hive to stasis.

18
00:00:52.052 --> 00:00:53.246
I'll be in touch.

19
00:00:53.420 --> 00:00:55.513
Ugh. Do you have a roommate?

20
00:00:55.688 --> 00:00:57.519
- No.
- Don't get one. Ever.

21
00:00:57.690 --> 00:00:59.214
Trouble in paradise?

22
00:00:59.392 --> 00:01:01.553
Well. nothing a good exterminator
couldn't solve.

23
00:01:01.728 --> 00:01:04.720
- Tonight still a good night to talk?
- Yeah. let's just get out of here.

24
00:01:04.898 --> 00:01:07.696
I need coffee
that wasn't made by a cop.

25
00:01:08.601 --> 00:01:11.069
Three neighborhood
drugstores. all in my precinct.

26
00:01:11.237 --> 00:01:13.501
all robbed in the last month.

27
00:01:15.608 --> 00:01:17.542
None of the stores had
security cameras

28
00:01:17.710 --> 00:01:20.611
but all the robberies took place
when the owners were closing up.

29
00:01:21.181 --> 00:01:23.012
Descriptions of the perps match
in all three.

30
00:01:23.183 --> 00:01:25.014
and also. they only took
prescription pills.

31
00:01:25.185 --> 00:01:28.120
High street value.
Oxy. hydrocodone.

32
00:01:28.621 --> 00:01:31.215
Sounds like it was all done
by the same crew.

33
00:01:31.391 --> 00:01:35.293
I've been re-interviewing witnesses.
putting in extra hours.

34
00:01:35.462 --> 00:01:38.226
keeping an eye
on the other stores but. uh.

35
00:01:38.398 --> 00:01:39.660
I'm not making much headway.

36
00:01:40.900 --> 00:01:43.027
Is there a detective on this case?

37
00:01:44.104 --> 00:01:45.901
Hanford.

38
00:01:46.873 --> 00:01:51.333
I'm not trying to step on his toes. I'm...
I don't want to be disrespectful but...

39
00:01:53.713 --> 00:01:56.648
But his plate's kind of full right now.

40
00:01:57.750 --> 00:02:00.583
It's my neighborhood.
My partner and I. we...

41
00:02:00.753 --> 00:02:03.586
We have to look these people
in the eye every day.

42
00:02:04.224 --> 00:02:07.887
They're scared.
It would mean a lot to them.

43
00:02:08.294 --> 00:02:10.091
A lot to me.
if I could bring this one home.

44
00:02:12.165 --> 00:02:14.326
All right. I'll take a look.

45
00:02:14.501 --> 00:02:16.799
Um. I'll let you know
if anything comes up.

46
00:02:21.374 --> 00:02:23.433
I know it's late here.

47
00:02:25.078 --> 00:02:26.909
Well. you wanted to go
to school out west. no?

48
00:02:27.080 --> 00:02:29.640
Or is it just that I'm keeping you
from a party?

49
00:02:37.023 --> 00:02:40.015
Hey. I'm sorry. Yeah. some drunk idiot
and he almost hit me.

50
00:02:40.193 --> 00:02:43.185
No. no. no. I'm fine. I'm fine.
I guess the bars must be letting out.

51
00:02:45.000 --> 00:02:51.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

52
00:02:57.143 --> 00:02:58.303
What the hell?

53
00:03:02.549 --> 00:03:03.982
Hey!

54
00:03:06.119 --> 00:03:07.609
Hey!

55
00:03:08.922 --> 00:03:11.482
Hey. man. what's wrong?

56
00:03:37.951 --> 00:03:40.943
What a drunk idiot.
I tell you. man.

57
00:03:41.454 --> 00:03:43.388
you had an angel looking out
for you tonight.

58
00:03:54.000 --> 00:04:02.000
<b><font color=#004F8C>Ripped By mstoll</b></font>

59
00:04:21.160 --> 00:04:24.288
- You said you knew this guy.
- I was an admirer.

60
00:04:25.164 --> 00:04:28.531
Garrison Boyd was president of the
Five Boroughs Sceptics Association.

61
00:04:29.435 --> 00:04:31.494
He was a debunker
of the highest order.

62
00:04:31.671 --> 00:04:35.437
He was a bright light of reason in a sea
of gullibility and magical thought.

63
00:04:37.176 --> 00:04:40.304
- He was a professional doubter.
- Of?

64
00:04:40.480 --> 00:04:43.278
Pseudoscience. the paranormal.
organized religion.

65
00:04:43.449 --> 00:04:47.351
All the usual bollocks.
He wrote a blog that I rather enjoyed.

66
00:04:47.553 --> 00:04:49.020
Did he believe in crowbars?

67
00:04:49.188 --> 00:04:53.454
Because I'm pretty sure
that's what caved his skull in.

68
00:04:59.565 --> 00:05:01.692
You put the time of death
at approximately one hour

69
00:05:01.868 --> 00:05:03.130
before his car was found.

70
00:05:03.703 --> 00:05:06.638
I'm guessing whoever killed him was
hoping that the impact of the train

71
00:05:06.806 --> 00:05:08.637
would hide the real cause of death.

72
00:05:10.109 --> 00:05:12.168
It says here you removed a small.
conical object

73
00:05:12.345 --> 00:05:16.782
- from beneath his right eye socket.
- After he was struck. he fell forward.

74
00:05:17.817 --> 00:05:21.116
This got wedged under his eye
on the way down.

75
00:05:21.688 --> 00:05:23.679
Don't know what it is.
I'm sending it to the lab.

76
00:05:23.856 --> 00:05:25.221
It's the tip of a hat.

77
00:05:26.959 --> 00:05:30.326
You are familiar with the vile practice
of lawn ornamentation?

78
00:05:30.496 --> 00:05:33.488
The worst offenders employ garden
gnomes. yea big. white beards...

79
00:05:33.666 --> 00:05:35.998
- Pointy red hats.
- If he wasn't so dead.

80
00:05:36.169 --> 00:05:39.195
I suspect Mr. Boyd would find it ironic
that a diminutive wood spirit

81
00:05:39.372 --> 00:05:41.465
played a role in his murder.

82
00:05:44.143 --> 00:05:46.304
He was particularly aggressive
in his pursuit of those

83
00:05:46.479 --> 00:05:51.007
who sought to profit
from their hoaxes. so...

84
00:05:51.184 --> 00:05:54.312
Perhaps his persistence
is the reason he now lies here.

85
00:05:54.487 --> 00:05:56.478
Think being debunked
is a reason to kill somebody?

86
00:05:56.656 --> 00:05:59.022
Some of the most aggressive
correspondence on his web site

87
00:05:59.192 --> 00:06:03.492
came from local ghost tour operators.
hawkers of phony medical cures.

88
00:06:03.663 --> 00:06:08.191
I think one recent exposé target might
have not so much a reasonable motive

89
00:06:08.368 --> 00:06:11.496
for murder as a lower standard
for committing one.

90
00:06:12.238 --> 00:06:14.263
Because he's almost certainly insane.

91
00:06:18.044 --> 00:06:22.105
I won't pretend that Mr. Boyd and I
didn't have a contentious relationship.

92
00:06:22.281 --> 00:06:25.045
He took issue with the church
on more than one occasion.

93
00:06:25.218 --> 00:06:27.948
You mean.
he took issue with your cult.

94
00:06:28.421 --> 00:06:31.049
He misused that term as well.

95
00:06:31.224 --> 00:06:33.419
That's just the kind of rigid.
closed-minded thinking

96
00:06:33.593 --> 00:06:35.060
that I preach against here.

97
00:06:35.228 --> 00:06:39.255
At one time or another. every great
religion has been attacked as a cult.

98
00:06:39.432 --> 00:06:40.922
So have most cults.

99
00:06:45.738 --> 00:06:48.707
- Excuse me for a minute. would you?
- Where are you...?

100
00:06:48.875 --> 00:06:51.708
Look. the victim published almost
two dozen threatening responses

101
00:06:51.878 --> 00:06:53.937
you sent him.
after he posted a few articles

102
00:06:54.113 --> 00:06:56.581
criticizing the church's
recruitment methods.

103
00:06:56.749 --> 00:06:59.274
Well. I have the right to respond.
if somebody publishes lies

104
00:06:59.452 --> 00:07:00.919
about what we're trying to do here.

105
00:07:01.087 --> 00:07:04.386
You told Mr. Boyd that his attacks
had begun a chain reaction

106
00:07:04.557 --> 00:07:08.323
that would lead to
"his removal from this physical reality."

107
00:07:08.494 --> 00:07:12.396
We meditate here.
We practice energy transference.

108
00:07:12.565 --> 00:07:14.260
So when I wrote to him.
I was merely

109
00:07:14.434 --> 00:07:17.926
absorbing his hateful energy
and reflecting it back.

110
00:07:18.104 --> 00:07:20.129
Did I harm him physically? No.

111
00:07:20.306 --> 00:07:24.072
Did I appeal to the quantum source
for swift and final justice? Perhaps.

112
00:07:24.243 --> 00:07:27.644
In other words.
you prayed for the guy to die.

113
00:07:27.814 --> 00:07:30.442
- That's not a crime. is it?
- So we're done here.

114
00:07:30.616 --> 00:07:32.641
The church held
a 12-hour service last night.

115
00:07:32.819 --> 00:07:36.482
Attendance was mandatory. so no one
here could have killed Garrison Boyd.

116
00:07:36.656 --> 00:07:38.624
We're just taking
your new friend's word for it?

117
00:07:38.791 --> 00:07:40.759
Her name is Aria. And yes. we are.

118
00:07:40.927 --> 00:07:43.691
When it became clear this one
would do little more than proselytize.

119
00:07:43.863 --> 00:07:46.957
I scanned his herd and realized
that Aria was having second thoughts

120
00:07:47.133 --> 00:07:49.863
- about being here.
- Aria's a level-three conduit.

121
00:07:50.036 --> 00:07:53.665
After a brief conversation with Aria.
a.k.a. Elizabeth Weinberg.

122
00:07:53.840 --> 00:07:56.331
I was able to determine
that some unresolved issues

123
00:07:56.509 --> 00:07:58.306
from her childhood
had led to a transference

124
00:07:58.478 --> 00:08:00.639
of a need for structure
and discipline onto Mr. Finn.

125
00:08:00.813 --> 00:08:03.373
Elizabeth agreed. and has forthwith
terminated her relationship

126
00:08:03.549 --> 00:08:04.948
- with your church.
- What?

127
00:08:05.117 --> 00:08:06.812
Are you saying
you deprogrammed her?

128
00:08:06.986 --> 00:08:09.147
I would never use such a rigid
and closed-minded term.

129
00:08:09.322 --> 00:08:12.291
She did. however. share some useful
information on the church's methods.

130
00:08:12.458 --> 00:08:16.326
Apparently. their esteemed leader likes
to send his acolytes out to follow.

131
00:08:16.496 --> 00:08:19.897
photograph and harass people
who dare to criticize him.

132
00:08:20.066 --> 00:08:22.159
So she's currently in your office.
e-mailing me

133
00:08:22.335 --> 00:08:24.496
the dossier you compiled
on Garrison Boyd.

134
00:08:24.670 --> 00:08:27.662
I'm hopeful it will shed some
additional light on his final days.

135
00:08:28.774 --> 00:08:30.401
Ms. Weinberg is leaving with us.

136
00:08:30.576 --> 00:08:33.136
Any attempt to hinder
her return to her former life

137
00:08:33.312 --> 00:08:36.179
will be met with an energy
transference most unpleasant.

138
00:08:40.152 --> 00:08:41.983
- Joan.
- Oh. hey.

139
00:08:42.154 --> 00:08:44.019
Heard you were helping Hannah
with something.

140
00:08:44.190 --> 00:08:48.559
Yeah. there's been some robberies
in her precinct. She wants to help.

141
00:08:48.728 --> 00:08:51.219
- You sure it's not a bother?
- No. not at all.

142
00:08:51.397 --> 00:08:54.059
I got into it this morning
and now I'm helping Sherlock

143
00:08:54.233 --> 00:08:56.599
with this homicide he's working.

144
00:08:56.802 --> 00:08:59.862
Just make sure she knows whose
consultant you really are.

145
00:09:00.039 --> 00:09:01.836
All right.

146
00:09:10.850 --> 00:09:13.216
So when were you going to inform me
that we're assisting

147
00:09:13.386 --> 00:09:16.617
- Hannah Gregson on a case?
- You could hear all that?

148
00:09:17.857 --> 00:09:21.520
We aren't helping her. okay?
I am. And it's not a secret.

149
00:09:21.694 --> 00:09:24.595
I'm just gonna run down a lead or two.
It shouldn't take too much time.

150
00:09:24.764 --> 00:09:26.026
It took time this morning.

151
00:09:26.599 --> 00:09:28.123
So is this everything
from the church?

152
00:09:28.334 --> 00:09:30.734
It is a testament to the insidiousness
of cult thinking:

153
00:09:30.903 --> 00:09:33.565
A charismatic loon like Finn warps
impressionable minds

154
00:09:33.739 --> 00:09:36.936
and then sends them to stalk
and harass.

155
00:09:37.109 --> 00:09:39.634
And here I thought they just
sold flowers at the airport.

156
00:09:39.845 --> 00:09:41.779
I find the practice repulsive.
but in this case.

157
00:09:41.948 --> 00:09:43.575
it may have played in our favor.

158
00:09:44.150 --> 00:09:46.618
Two cult members were assigned
to Garrison Boyd in the weeks

159
00:09:46.786 --> 00:09:49.653
before his murder.
Thanks to their long lenses

160
00:09:49.855 --> 00:09:54.292
and meticulous note-taking.
we may have a person of interest

161
00:09:54.460 --> 00:09:58.123
a man by the name of Collin Eisely.

162
00:09:59.599 --> 00:10:02.466
I'm sorry.
I need to catch up a little. here.

163
00:10:02.635 --> 00:10:04.660
Have I been under police
surveillance?

164
00:10:04.870 --> 00:10:08.067
No. those were taken by someone
who was interested in that man.

165
00:10:08.240 --> 00:10:09.264
Garrison Boyd.

166
00:10:09.442 --> 00:10:12.275
We have hundreds of
photographs. in all manner of activities.

167
00:10:12.445 --> 00:10:14.470
Those are the only ones
where he appears to be

168
00:10:14.647 --> 00:10:18.481
in heated altercation with a man
two days before he was murdered.

169
00:10:18.651 --> 00:10:20.949
- This guy was murdered?
- Last night.

170
00:10:21.120 --> 00:10:22.747
Do you wanna tell us
how you knew him?

171
00:10:22.922 --> 00:10:24.685
I didn't. Uh...

172
00:10:24.890 --> 00:10:27.654
The day these were taken. he was
waiting for me outside my building.

173
00:10:27.827 --> 00:10:29.419
I'd never seen him before.

174
00:10:30.930 --> 00:10:32.192
I'm confused.

175
00:10:32.398 --> 00:10:35.993
Does being accosted by a lunatic
make me a murder suspect?

176
00:10:36.168 --> 00:10:37.692
That depends
on why he accosted you.

177
00:10:39.505 --> 00:10:40.995
I'm in real estate.

178
00:10:41.173 --> 00:10:44.370
Late last year. I looked at some beach
properties out on Long Island.

179
00:10:44.543 --> 00:10:47.205
I made this woman an offer
on her house. she said no.

180
00:10:47.413 --> 00:10:52.282
A few months later. this nut comes
out of the woodwork and accuses me

181
00:10:52.451 --> 00:10:56.046
- of trying to scare her into moving.
- Scare her how?

182
00:10:56.222 --> 00:10:59.385
According to him.
she was hearing things in her house.

183
00:10:59.558 --> 00:11:01.958
Voices. banging. I don't know.

184
00:11:02.128 --> 00:11:04.688
She thought it was ghosts.
he thought it was me.

185
00:11:04.864 --> 00:11:06.832
- Was it?
- Of course not.

186
00:11:06.999 --> 00:11:09.524
She didn't wanna sell. I moved on.
end of story.

187
00:11:09.702 --> 00:11:14.662
Mm. I see you've amassed. um.
quite an art collection here. Mr. Eisely.

188
00:11:14.840 --> 00:11:17.070
That's an interest that requires
a great deal of money

189
00:11:17.243 --> 00:11:18.972
and a very competitive spirit.

190
00:11:19.145 --> 00:11:22.308
I imagine you're not the sort of person
who takes no for an answer very often.

191
00:11:22.481 --> 00:11:25.143
I'm also not the sort who goes around
scaring little old ladies.

192
00:11:25.651 --> 00:11:27.346
Can you tell us
where you were last night

193
00:11:27.520 --> 00:11:29.511
between the hours
of 10 p.m. And midnight?

194
00:11:29.689 --> 00:11:31.987
At a retirement party for a friend.

195
00:11:32.158 --> 00:11:34.023
A few of us went out
for drinks after that.

196
00:11:36.228 --> 00:11:38.093
I'll get you their names and numbers.

197
00:11:44.403 --> 00:11:46.496
If that guy was interested
in the property.

198
00:11:46.672 --> 00:11:49.038
there's a possibility
that other developers were too.

199
00:11:49.208 --> 00:11:52.075
You're wondering if one of them
gaslit the owner.

200
00:11:52.244 --> 00:11:54.542
then killed Boyd.
lest he expose them?

201
00:11:55.081 --> 00:11:57.845
Makes more sense than ghosts.
doesn't it?

202
00:11:58.017 --> 00:12:01.976
Well. I wouldn't say "ghosts." plural.

203
00:12:03.222 --> 00:12:07.921
It was my husband. Harry.
I know because I heard him.

204
00:12:08.094 --> 00:12:09.561
He was talking to me.

205
00:12:11.197 --> 00:12:15.463
- Your husband passed away?
- Oh. coming up on a year now.

206
00:12:15.634 --> 00:12:19.229
We know that Colin Eisely made an
offer on the house a few months ago.

207
00:12:19.405 --> 00:12:21.066
Did anyone else approach you?

208
00:12:21.240 --> 00:12:23.800
Yes. once.
but that was almost 20 years go.

209
00:12:24.009 --> 00:12:26.375
I don't think that company
is even in business now.

210
00:12:26.545 --> 00:12:28.979
Did you tell anyone else about
the voices you were hearing?

211
00:12:29.148 --> 00:12:30.809
Only my daughter.

212
00:12:31.016 --> 00:12:34.417
She was the one who called
that poor man. Mr. Boyd.

213
00:12:34.587 --> 00:12:38.580
And she wanted him to convince me
that I was imagining things.

214
00:12:39.525 --> 00:12:42.619
She has such a literal mind.

215
00:12:42.795 --> 00:12:45.161
I've always told her
she should be more open.

216
00:12:45.331 --> 00:12:46.889
So she didn't hear the voice.

217
00:12:48.234 --> 00:12:50.998
And she never heard any
of Harry's tantrums. either.

218
00:12:51.170 --> 00:12:53.900
- Tantrums?
- He knocked some glasses out

219
00:12:54.073 --> 00:12:57.042
of that cabinet there.
Lights flickered.

220
00:12:57.576 --> 00:13:00.477
Sometimes.
he shook the whole house.

221
00:13:00.646 --> 00:13:03.774
Oh. he was angry.
and he was letting me know.

222
00:13:04.683 --> 00:13:06.844
And why would he have been angry?

223
00:13:07.052 --> 00:13:10.681
Sometimes we had an open marriage.

224
00:13:10.856 --> 00:13:12.289
Other times we didn't.

225
00:13:12.458 --> 00:13:17.157
And when we didn't. I did some things
that I never told him about.

226
00:13:18.430 --> 00:13:21.297
And now that he's dead.
he knows everything.

227
00:13:21.467 --> 00:13:26.166
That's quite a one-two punch. isn't it?
Discovering you're dead and a cuckold.

228
00:13:26.338 --> 00:13:29.330
It doesn't bother me
that you don't believe me.

229
00:13:30.476 --> 00:13:34.344
I fear that I too.
may be cursed with a literal mind.

230
00:13:34.513 --> 00:13:37.346
If. however.
you are not experiencing delusions.

231
00:13:37.516 --> 00:13:40.349
it may be possible that someone
is trying to take advantage of you.

232
00:13:41.120 --> 00:13:43.816
You said Harry spoke to you.
what did he say?

233
00:13:44.456 --> 00:13:49.689
I have it on tape.
You could listen for yourself.

234
00:13:51.096 --> 00:13:55.499
The clearest I ever heard Harry's voice
was when I was down here.

235
00:13:55.668 --> 00:13:59.104
so I started leaving my tape recorder
on all the time.

236
00:14:00.472 --> 00:14:03.532
You have to turn the volume
all the way up to hear his voice.

237
00:14:08.614 --> 00:14:11.139
- <i>Im haram.</i>
- No. no.

238
00:14:11.317 --> 00:14:14.980
He's saying a name. Jim Harmon.

239
00:14:15.154 --> 00:14:17.315
That's the man I had the affair with.

240
00:14:17.489 --> 00:14:20.014
Harry really shook
the whole house that night.

241
00:14:20.192 --> 00:14:23.127
And then he started yelling
Jim's name.

242
00:14:32.238 --> 00:14:34.763
Well. do you still think
I'm imagining things?

243
00:14:34.940 --> 00:14:37.636
I apologize. Mrs. Renziger.
You most certainly are not.

244
00:14:38.944 --> 00:14:42.402
You mentioned that some glasses
were knocked off the cabinet upstairs.

245
00:14:42.581 --> 00:14:44.606
That cabinet rests against
this wall. yes?

246
00:14:44.783 --> 00:14:46.751
Yes. the living room is right above it.

247
00:15:01.901 --> 00:15:04.028
How well do you know
your neighbors?

248
00:15:04.203 --> 00:15:05.261
Jerry and Paula?

249
00:15:05.437 --> 00:15:07.803
They moved in here about
the same time as I did.

250
00:15:08.607 --> 00:15:09.699
But they're snowbirds.

251
00:15:09.875 --> 00:15:12.309
They won't be back from Florida
for a few more weeks.

252
00:15:12.478 --> 00:15:16.278
Well. good neighbors
often exchange keys.

253
00:15:16.448 --> 00:15:19.906
Are you a good neighbor.
Mrs. Renziger?

254
00:15:21.720 --> 00:15:26.419
The voice on the recording did not say
"Jim Harmon" it said <i>"im haram."</i>

255
00:15:26.592 --> 00:15:29.083
It's a common Arabic obscenity.

256
00:15:29.261 --> 00:15:31.752
So you think that voice was coming
from all the way over here

257
00:15:31.931 --> 00:15:33.262
in the neighbor's basement.

258
00:15:33.432 --> 00:15:37.334
No. I think someone shortened
the distance considerably.

259
00:15:39.071 --> 00:15:42.165
Along with the voice.
I heard a distinct banging

260
00:15:42.341 --> 00:15:45.401
and a low rumbling frequency
on the recording.

261
00:15:45.577 --> 00:15:48.171
That. along with the rest
of Mrs. Renziger's account.

262
00:15:48.347 --> 00:15:51.805
the. uh. vibrations.
the flickering lights.

263
00:15:51.984 --> 00:15:56.751
all suggest that someone
was employing digging equipment

264
00:15:56.922 --> 00:15:59.584
near the foundation of her home.

265
00:16:01.794 --> 00:16:03.625
There were no signs
of digging outside.

266
00:16:03.796 --> 00:16:06.356
so you think it was all happening
down here?

267
00:16:21.547 --> 00:16:23.777
Is that a tunnel?

268
00:16:28.187 --> 00:16:30.621
With a termination point somewhere
near the foundation

269
00:16:30.789 --> 00:16:33.121
of Mrs. Renziger's home.

270
00:16:33.292 --> 00:16:37.752
Why would someone do all this.
dig from this basement to hers?

271
00:16:38.530 --> 00:16:40.760
I know a way to find out.

272
00:17:00.719 --> 00:17:04.519
- Did you find anything?
- I have. indeed.

273
00:17:05.057 --> 00:17:07.855
Mrs. Renziger was not visited
by her husband's ghost.

274
00:17:09.395 --> 00:17:12.694
She may. however.
have been visited by terrorists.

275
00:17:20.506 --> 00:17:24.499
Meet Ruby.
She's a transatlantic data cable.

276
00:17:24.676 --> 00:17:26.576
The fastest in the world

277
00:17:26.745 --> 00:17:29.543
and a backbone
of the North American Internet.

278
00:17:29.715 --> 00:17:30.875
She looks like a garden hose.

279
00:17:31.050 --> 00:17:33.450
It's a curse of the modern age
that very significant things

280
00:17:33.619 --> 00:17:35.746
appear commonplace.
Now. Ruby is one of several

281
00:17:35.921 --> 00:17:39.254
undersea cables which connects
Europe to the United States.

282
00:17:39.825 --> 00:17:42.350
The full spectrum of commerce
and communication flows

283
00:17:42.528 --> 00:17:43.927
through her optic fibers.

284
00:17:44.096 --> 00:17:47.031
as well as the requisite glut
of pornography and cat videos.

285
00:17:47.533 --> 00:17:50.593
And you knew that
was what that cable was how?

286
00:17:50.769 --> 00:17:52.862
The location of such cables is mapped.

287
00:17:53.038 --> 00:17:55.472
They're accessible
with very little effort.

288
00:17:55.641 --> 00:18:00.476
The intent is to avoid entanglements
and utility mishaps.

289
00:18:00.646 --> 00:18:02.773
but it also makes them amongst
the most vulnerable

290
00:18:02.948 --> 00:18:05.382
terrorist targets in the world.

291
00:18:05.551 --> 00:18:08.315
And this basement's probably
a pretty smart place to dig from.

292
00:18:08.487 --> 00:18:10.648
And anywhere along the beach
would attract attention.

293
00:18:10.856 --> 00:18:12.721
out in the ocean would be
a lot harder.

294
00:18:12.891 --> 00:18:16.122
And the cable ties into a landing house
another quarter of a mile inland.

295
00:18:16.295 --> 00:18:18.490
at which point security increases
markedly.

296
00:18:18.664 --> 00:18:21.929
What our attackers did not account
for was the intrusion of Garrison Boyd.

297
00:18:22.101 --> 00:18:25.229
Right. so someone runs tunneling
equipment out of the Ayers' basement

298
00:18:25.404 --> 00:18:26.837
while they're away for the winter.

299
00:18:27.005 --> 00:18:29.735
Mrs. Renziger hears the noise
and thinks it's her dead husband.

300
00:18:29.908 --> 00:18:31.933
so her daughter asks Boyd
to prove otherwise.

301
00:18:32.111 --> 00:18:35.638
and then Boyd finds all this.
same way you and Joan did?

302
00:18:40.619 --> 00:18:44.612
This little fella was amongst
the gardening equipment over there.

303
00:18:44.790 --> 00:18:46.087
The tip of his hat is missing.

304
00:18:49.495 --> 00:18:51.326
Mr. Boyd was murdered in this room.

305
00:18:51.497 --> 00:18:53.965
The killer loads the body
into Boyd's car.

306
00:18:54.133 --> 00:18:56.294
drives it back into the city.
but then what?

307
00:18:56.468 --> 00:18:58.527
Why not come back
and cut the cable?

308
00:18:58.704 --> 00:19:01.332
Figured Boyd found them.
someone else might be coming too?

309
00:19:01.507 --> 00:19:05.102
Perhaps. Or perhaps the fact
that Ruby has not been cut

310
00:19:05.277 --> 00:19:06.801
signals a much greater threat.

311
00:19:07.813 --> 00:19:09.781
The Internet is designed
with redundancies.

312
00:19:09.948 --> 00:19:13.111
Cutting a single cable
would no doubt cause some problems.

313
00:19:13.285 --> 00:19:16.550
but a coordinated attack.
that could be crippling.

314
00:19:17.156 --> 00:19:19.716
You think there might be other guys
digging up other cables.

315
00:19:19.925 --> 00:19:21.722
waiting for a signal to cut them
all at once?

316
00:19:22.227 --> 00:19:24.491
I think it's a possibility
that we should consider.

317
00:19:24.663 --> 00:19:29.623
I'll reach out to DHS.
Let them know what's going on.

318
00:19:35.374 --> 00:19:37.467
I'll check back with you.

319
00:19:38.677 --> 00:19:39.769
So you were right.

320
00:19:39.945 --> 00:19:42.072
Whoever dug that tunnel stuck
mostly to the basement.

321
00:19:42.247 --> 00:19:44.715
- They did come here now and then.
- Yes. naturally.

322
00:19:44.883 --> 00:19:47.750
If the man or men or women
were here to do arduous work.

323
00:19:47.953 --> 00:19:50.820
the hours would have been long.
they would have needed to eat.

324
00:19:50.989 --> 00:19:52.513
hydrate and. of course.
expel waste.

325
00:19:52.691 --> 00:19:55.592
Toilet seat was up. so I'm guessing
at least one person was a "he."

326
00:19:55.761 --> 00:19:59.754
Also we found this in the fridge.

327
00:20:00.499 --> 00:20:04.560
Doogh. Carbonated yogurt drink
popular in Arab countries.

328
00:20:04.736 --> 00:20:07.534
It's hard to believe bubbling yogurt
is popular anywhere.

329
00:20:07.706 --> 00:20:10.869
I figured it didn't belong to the Ayers.
so I called the American distributor.

330
00:20:11.043 --> 00:20:13.944
No place on the island sells it.
Six stores in the city do.

331
00:20:14.112 --> 00:20:16.376
They're e-mailing me a list.

332
00:20:16.548 --> 00:20:18.516
Assuming these stores
have surveillance cameras.

333
00:20:18.684 --> 00:20:21.016
we can check their footage
from the last few weeks.

334
00:20:21.186 --> 00:20:23.711
see if anyone jumps out.

335
00:20:23.889 --> 00:20:25.754
Hannah. come in.

336
00:20:29.561 --> 00:20:33.122
- So I have good news.
- Don't tell me you solved it already.

337
00:20:33.298 --> 00:20:35.596
Actually. you already had
all the pieces.

338
00:20:35.767 --> 00:20:38.895
Now. you said that all three drugstores
were robbed around closing time.

339
00:20:39.071 --> 00:20:41.596
At first. I assumed
what you probably did.

340
00:20:41.773 --> 00:20:44.367
That it was because closing
is when a store is most vulnerable.

341
00:20:44.543 --> 00:20:47.569
No customers. fewer employees.
most cash on hand.

342
00:20:47.746 --> 00:20:50.237
But in this case.
there was something else.

343
00:20:50.415 --> 00:20:53.213
Now. two of the pharmacists told you
that a candy-machine vendor

344
00:20:53.385 --> 00:20:55.376
had come by just before
the robberies.

345
00:20:55.554 --> 00:21:00.321
I checked. and that same vendor
has machines in all three stores.

346
00:21:00.525 --> 00:21:01.890
You think the vendor's in on it.

347
00:21:02.060 --> 00:21:05.291
He scopes out the stores and then
tells his accomplices if it's all clear.

348
00:21:06.565 --> 00:21:08.556
A friend took these today.

349
00:21:08.734 --> 00:21:10.964
Vending machine company uses
this warehouse to store

350
00:21:11.136 --> 00:21:14.071
their inventory and do repairs.
Look at these guys.

351
00:21:14.606 --> 00:21:17.404
Height. hair color. visible tattoos.

352
00:21:18.543 --> 00:21:20.477
They match the descriptions
of the three perps.

353
00:21:20.646 --> 00:21:23.274
They definitely don't look like
they're in the gumball business.

354
00:21:23.448 --> 00:21:28.408
Mm. You found them. I can't believe it.
I mean. I can. I'm not surprised.

355
00:21:28.587 --> 00:21:29.849
But thank you.

356
00:21:30.656 --> 00:21:33.420
Odds are. this is where
they're storing the stolen pills.

357
00:21:33.592 --> 00:21:35.253
When you bring this
to Detective Hanford.

358
00:21:35.427 --> 00:21:36.917
feel free to leave my name out of it.

359
00:21:37.095 --> 00:21:39.029
My guess is.
the department's gonna wanna sit

360
00:21:39.197 --> 00:21:40.858
- on this place for a while.
- Why?

361
00:21:41.667 --> 00:21:44.158
As long as it doesn't look like
another robbery is imminent.

362
00:21:44.336 --> 00:21:46.668
they're gonna want to follow
the drugs up the food chain.

363
00:21:46.838 --> 00:21:48.829
With the amount of pills
these guys are stealing.

364
00:21:49.007 --> 00:21:52.875
they probably have help moving them.
So this could lead to bigger fish.

365
00:21:58.450 --> 00:22:00.941
Took no small amount of negotiation.
but I was able to procure

366
00:22:01.119 --> 00:22:03.280
security footage from each
of the doogh-selling

367
00:22:03.455 --> 00:22:05.150
ethnic markets that you identified.

368
00:22:05.324 --> 00:22:08.293
Now. taking into account the hours
Claire Renziger did and did not

369
00:22:08.460 --> 00:22:11.327
hear ghosts. it would appear
that our tunneler kept hours

370
00:22:11.496 --> 00:22:13.191
between 8 to 6.

371
00:22:13.365 --> 00:22:15.299
So it stands to reason
that he bought his doogh

372
00:22:15.467 --> 00:22:18.095
and other provisions at either
the beginning or end of each day.

373
00:22:18.637 --> 00:22:22.334
Oh. that's great.
It'll help us move through these faster.

374
00:22:22.507 --> 00:22:24.532
Assuming you're not still
splitting your time

375
00:22:24.710 --> 00:22:27.804
between the tribulations of a beat cop
and the hunt for a likely terrorist.

376
00:22:27.979 --> 00:22:30.812
May I remind you that "beat cop"
is our boss's daughter?

377
00:22:30.982 --> 00:22:33.007
Is that why you were helping her?
To curry favor?

378
00:22:33.185 --> 00:22:35.312
I'm helping her
because she asked me.

379
00:22:36.421 --> 00:22:40.255
- What do you think of her?
- Hannah? She's nice.

380
00:22:40.425 --> 00:22:42.325
What do you think of her
as an investigator?

381
00:22:43.228 --> 00:22:45.025
Oh. she's green.
I mean. she's dedicated.

382
00:22:45.197 --> 00:22:47.722
She did all the legwork.
she just couldn't connect the dots.

383
00:22:47.899 --> 00:22:49.526
- Why?
- Oh. it just confirms

384
00:22:49.701 --> 00:22:51.999
a long-held suspicion.
She's middling.

385
00:22:52.170 --> 00:22:53.865
Hold on. I did not say
she was middling.

386
00:22:54.039 --> 00:22:56.200
That's sad. because
she is the daughter of a colleague

387
00:22:56.375 --> 00:22:57.933
and he has certain aspirations
for her.

388
00:22:58.143 --> 00:23:00.543
Excuse me. but have you ever
even talked to Hannah?

389
00:23:00.712 --> 00:23:01.736
- Twice.
- That's it?

390
00:23:01.913 --> 00:23:05.508
- That all you needed to size her up?
- I also looked at her records.

391
00:23:05.684 --> 00:23:08.585
Understand. Watson: I think she's
a perfectly capable police officer.

392
00:23:08.754 --> 00:23:10.847
She knows how to handle herself
in a confrontation.

393
00:23:11.022 --> 00:23:12.216
First-rate with a weapon.

394
00:23:12.391 --> 00:23:14.359
What I fear she is not. however.
is a detective.

395
00:23:14.559 --> 00:23:15.856
Give me a break.

396
00:23:16.027 --> 00:23:18.359
It's a calling. Watson.
No one knows that better than you.

397
00:23:18.964 --> 00:23:20.295
I learned because you taught me.

398
00:23:20.465 --> 00:23:22.023
I taught you
because I saw something.

399
00:23:22.200 --> 00:23:24.225
What if I told you I see something
in Hannah?

400
00:23:24.403 --> 00:23:29.306
- I would tell you you're mistaken.
- You know what? I'll be in my room.

401
00:23:50.896 --> 00:23:54.662
<i>Thought I'd let you sleep in.
You found my notes?</i>

402
00:23:54.833 --> 00:23:56.664
Well. sort of hard to miss.

403
00:23:56.835 --> 00:24:00.236
- Watched the video?
- I take it this is our suspect?

404
00:24:00.405 --> 00:24:03.169
<i>Note the coveralls.
The tape you're watching</i>

405
00:24:03.341 --> 00:24:08.608
records his fifth appearance
at the store in a span of two weeks.

406
00:24:09.281 --> 00:24:12.250
During that period of time.
his clothes get progressively dirtier.

407
00:24:12.417 --> 00:24:15.250
save for two rectangular spots
on his knees.

408
00:24:15.420 --> 00:24:18.150
Presumably. he wore some knee pads
while he was digging his tunnel.

409
00:24:18.323 --> 00:24:21.156
Well presumably isn't "definitely."
He may just be a plumber.

410
00:24:21.326 --> 00:24:23.123
And I see he didn't use his
credit card.

411
00:24:23.295 --> 00:24:26.196
<i>As is his wont. Unfortunately.
he can't be identified via receipts.</i>

412
00:24:26.364 --> 00:24:28.093
<i>The woman in the red coat.
however...</i>

413
00:24:28.867 --> 00:24:30.664
- She knows him.
- <i>She paid with her</i>

414
00:24:30.836 --> 00:24:31.860
<i>American Express.</i>

415
00:24:32.037 --> 00:24:36.098
Her name is Yolanda Massee and I'm
stepping into her elevator as we speak.

416
00:24:36.274 --> 00:24:38.970
I'll call you when I know more.

417
00:24:43.148 --> 00:24:44.979
- Yes?
- Hello.

418
00:24:45.150 --> 00:24:46.947
Ms. Massee?
My name is Sherlock Holmes.

419
00:24:47.118 --> 00:24:49.018
I'm a consultant
with the New York Police.

420
00:24:49.187 --> 00:24:51.178
I was hoping I might ask you
a few questions.

421
00:24:51.356 --> 00:24:53.517
- Do you have a badge?
- I'm afraid I'm quite allergic

422
00:24:53.692 --> 00:24:57.150
to iconography. I was hoping you might
be able to tell me this man's name.

423
00:24:57.329 --> 00:24:59.797
- Heh. Is this a joke?
- No.

424
00:25:00.999 --> 00:25:04.560
I think it's Nazim or Nadim.
I'm not really sure.

425
00:25:04.769 --> 00:25:06.828
- But you know him?
- I don't know.

426
00:25:07.005 --> 00:25:08.632
How well do you know
your neighbors?

427
00:25:08.807 --> 00:25:11.139
- He's your neighbor?
- He lives right there.

428
00:25:19.985 --> 00:25:21.919
I'd recommend you leave
your building right now.

429
00:25:22.087 --> 00:25:23.486
What? Why?

430
00:25:23.655 --> 00:25:25.054
Your neighbor heard us talking

431
00:25:26.791 --> 00:25:29.817
And he is currently dousing
his apartment with accelerant.

432
00:25:29.995 --> 00:25:31.394
Go on!

433
00:25:34.933 --> 00:25:36.924
Nadim? Or is it Nazim?

434
00:25:37.102 --> 00:25:39.764
You might find this hard to believe.
but I'm here to help you.

435
00:25:39.938 --> 00:25:42.065
Don't come any closer.

436
00:25:43.508 --> 00:25:45.908
You're not a terrorist at all.
are you? No.

437
00:25:46.678 --> 00:25:48.908
I'm open to the possibility
that Garrison Boyd's death

438
00:25:49.080 --> 00:25:52.345
was an accident. He caught
you unawares and you panicked.

439
00:25:52.517 --> 00:25:55.509
But if you drop that lighter.
you will be attempting murder

440
00:25:55.687 --> 00:25:58.383
on the 200 or so other people
who live in this building.

441
00:26:16.608 --> 00:26:23.138
This contraption was at the heart of
the drawings on Nadim Al-Haj's walls.

442
00:26:23.348 --> 00:26:26.374
I only had a moment to absorb them
before they were engulfed in flames.

443
00:26:26.551 --> 00:26:31.147
but it was clear that he never intended
to sever the cable that he excavated.

444
00:26:31.356 --> 00:26:35.224
Rather. I think his plan
was to splice this device onto it.

445
00:26:36.561 --> 00:26:38.426
You think you can figure out
what it does?

446
00:26:38.597 --> 00:26:40.724
I won't know until we cut off
the melted plastic.

447
00:26:40.899 --> 00:26:43.561
but hopefully.
enough of the circuitry inside is intact.

448
00:26:43.735 --> 00:26:46.795
If I was a betting man. I'd say that
it was meant to collect information

449
00:26:46.972 --> 00:26:48.837
and transmit it elsewhere.

450
00:26:49.007 --> 00:26:51.100
You're thinking
this is one big data grab.

451
00:26:51.276 --> 00:26:52.971
Why not hack into it from a computer?

452
00:26:53.144 --> 00:26:55.442
There's gotta be an easier way
than digging that tunnel.

453
00:26:55.981 --> 00:26:57.949
Ask the NSA.
According to Edward Snowden.

454
00:26:58.116 --> 00:27:01.244
U.S. Intelligence agencies routinely tap
into these cables upstream

455
00:27:01.419 --> 00:27:04.354
of their official tie-ins so they can
better monitor American citizens.

456
00:27:04.522 --> 00:27:07.980
The first time Ruby feeds aboveground
is at 60 Hudson. downtown.

457
00:27:08.159 --> 00:27:10.491
Big banks have offices there
to get financial data first.

458
00:27:10.662 --> 00:27:13.495
but it's also where a lot of info
gets encrypted and after that.

459
00:27:13.665 --> 00:27:15.462
it's harder to spy on.

460
00:27:15.634 --> 00:27:18.194
Actually. digging a hole on Long Island
makes a lot of sense.

461
00:27:18.403 --> 00:27:20.598
So you're saying my phone might
ring at any minute.

462
00:27:20.772 --> 00:27:22.637
telling me this guy works
for our government?

463
00:27:22.807 --> 00:27:25.037
Perhaps. Or a foreign one.
Or a corporation.

464
00:27:25.210 --> 00:27:27.644
Who in this day and age
does not view information as power?

465
00:27:27.812 --> 00:27:30.872
Hopefully. the device will tell us what
information the perp was capturing:

466
00:27:31.049 --> 00:27:33.483
E-mails. trade secrets.
credit-card numbers...

467
00:27:33.652 --> 00:27:36.712
If we're lucky. we'll even get
an IP address where it was being sent.

468
00:27:36.921 --> 00:27:40.357
Then we'll have a better idea
of what we're dealing with.

469
00:27:40.525 --> 00:27:46.122
Nadim Al-Haj. born in Iraq in 1978.
He emigrated to the U.S. In '06

470
00:27:46.297 --> 00:27:48.788
and became a citizen two years ago.

471
00:27:48.967 --> 00:27:50.798
He was an electrical engineer
in his country.

472
00:27:50.969 --> 00:27:53.460
but he's been working here
as a lineman for the cable company.

473
00:27:53.638 --> 00:27:54.969
So he definitely had the skills.

474
00:27:55.540 --> 00:27:57.531
Yeah. a few parking summonses

475
00:27:57.709 --> 00:28:00.075
but no criminal record
that I could find.

476
00:28:00.245 --> 00:28:03.510
- What's that about?
- Oh. you didn't hear?

477
00:28:03.715 --> 00:28:06.149
Hannah made a big collar
on her patrol this morning.

478
00:28:06.317 --> 00:28:08.308
Everyone's been messing
with the captain over it.

479
00:28:08.486 --> 00:28:10.215
- Oh. What'd she do?
- She spotted a perp

480
00:28:10.388 --> 00:28:13.824
who matched the description off
a few drugstore robberies on her beat.

481
00:28:13.992 --> 00:28:16.893
Now. he took off into a warehouse.
she and her partner followed.

482
00:28:17.062 --> 00:28:21.396
scooped him up and found
almost 200 grand worth of pills.

483
00:28:21.566 --> 00:28:23.932
- That's pretty lucky.
- Well. that ain't luck.

484
00:28:24.102 --> 00:28:27.401
That's DNA. She's good.

485
00:28:27.906 --> 00:28:30.739
Hey. you know. I just realized
I forgot. I have to run an errand.

486
00:28:30.909 --> 00:28:34.538
- Just tell Sherlock I'll catch up.
- All right.

487
00:28:37.415 --> 00:28:41.078
Captain. this is all we could find
on Nadim Al-Haj.

488
00:28:41.252 --> 00:28:45.120
It isn't much. Finest message
is out on him and his van.

489
00:28:45.290 --> 00:28:47.758
and Homeland Security's issued
a BOLO to Port Authority.

490
00:28:47.926 --> 00:28:49.393
Amtrak and TSA.

491
00:28:49.994 --> 00:28:53.191
The apartment Mr. Al-Haj occupied is
owned by "The Collin Eisely Group"?

492
00:28:54.399 --> 00:28:56.094
- You know that name?
- I do.

493
00:28:56.267 --> 00:28:58.428
Watson and I paid a visit
to Collin Eisely yesterday.

494
00:28:58.603 --> 00:29:00.070
He's a developer.

495
00:29:00.238 --> 00:29:02.297
Several months ago.
he made a bid on the house

496
00:29:02.507 --> 00:29:03.940
next to the one with the tunnel.

497
00:29:04.109 --> 00:29:06.600
You mean the one that's actually
much closer to the cable?

498
00:29:08.747 --> 00:29:12.615
The man who murdered Garrison Boyd
lives in a building that you own.

499
00:29:12.784 --> 00:29:16.311
What do you suppose the odds
are of that being a coincidence?

500
00:29:16.521 --> 00:29:19.820
I own several buildings. which.
together. house hundreds of tenants.

501
00:29:20.024 --> 00:29:23.425
It may surprise you to know I'm not on
a first-name basis with any of them.

502
00:29:23.595 --> 00:29:26.428
Interesting that you should mention
names. because you changed yours.

503
00:29:27.565 --> 00:29:29.931
Before you got into real estate.
you were a stockbroker.

504
00:29:30.101 --> 00:29:32.968
and until a few years ago.
your legal name was Louis Eisely.

505
00:29:33.605 --> 00:29:35.004
Collin was your middle name.

506
00:29:35.173 --> 00:29:37.641
We're guessing the decision
to change it has something to do

507
00:29:37.809 --> 00:29:39.834
with you serving 18 months
for insider trading?

508
00:29:40.044 --> 00:29:44.743
The name change was aboveboard.
I'm not breaking any laws.

509
00:29:44.916 --> 00:29:48.181
My real-estate dealings go much more
smoothly when my criminal record

510
00:29:48.353 --> 00:29:50.150
isn't the first thing people learn
about me.

511
00:29:50.321 --> 00:29:51.788
I imagine they would.

512
00:29:51.956 --> 00:29:54.686
Because Louis Eisely
was a particularly cutthroat

513
00:29:54.859 --> 00:29:58.260
Wall Street trader.
From the early 2000s.

514
00:29:58.429 --> 00:30:00.795
A man whose downfall.
at the height of his career.

515
00:30:00.965 --> 00:30:03.695
made his name synonymous
with Wall Street greed.

516
00:30:05.103 --> 00:30:08.436
I did my time. Prison changed me.

517
00:30:09.374 --> 00:30:10.864
I'm not so sure that it did.

518
00:30:11.109 --> 00:30:13.270
Trading in secrets put you on top.

519
00:30:13.444 --> 00:30:16.072
Does a man like you ever really
lose a taste for that?

520
00:30:17.148 --> 00:30:20.481
You still haven't explained
what it is you think I did.

521
00:30:20.652 --> 00:30:25.282
You hired Nadim Al-Haj to tap
a transatlantic data cable called Ruby.

522
00:30:25.456 --> 00:30:27.686
Runs right past
Claire Renziger's basement.

523
00:30:27.859 --> 00:30:31.386
So. first. you tried to buy her house.
When she turned you down.

524
00:30:31.596 --> 00:30:34.497
you had Al-Haj dig a tunnel
from next door. instead.

525
00:30:35.633 --> 00:30:37.624
And why would I have done
any of that?

526
00:30:37.802 --> 00:30:41.329
Because you have a savant's talent
for turning information into gold.

527
00:30:41.506 --> 00:30:42.666
Ruby is the motherlode.

528
00:30:42.841 --> 00:30:45.332
Tapping into her would give you
unfettered access to a wealth

529
00:30:45.510 --> 00:30:48.411
of intelligence with which to inform
your investment strategies.

530
00:30:49.347 --> 00:30:52.976
That's actually brilliant. I wish I had
thought of it back when I was trading.

531
00:30:53.151 --> 00:30:54.846
I can't go near the market.

532
00:30:55.019 --> 00:30:58.386
The SEC has banned me
from trading until the day I die.

533
00:30:58.556 --> 00:31:01.923
By court order. every dollar
I have in stocks is in a blind trust.

534
00:31:02.126 --> 00:31:03.184
You can look it up.

535
00:31:03.361 --> 00:31:05.556
Perhaps you're selling
the information for a price.

536
00:31:05.730 --> 00:31:08.699
And keep the proceeds where?
In my mattress?

537
00:31:08.867 --> 00:31:10.528
The Feds audit all my accounts.

538
00:31:10.702 --> 00:31:12.829
I can't win at bingo
without them taking notice.

539
00:31:14.706 --> 00:31:19.075
Gentlemen. I have more important
things to do with my day.

540
00:31:19.244 --> 00:31:23.078
You're fishing; I'm not biting.

541
00:31:26.651 --> 00:31:30.417
Hannah. I just heard the news.

542
00:31:30.588 --> 00:31:33.557
- Congratulations.
- Thanks.

543
00:31:34.025 --> 00:31:37.085
So I thought it was interesting how
you just happened to spot the suspect.

544
00:31:37.262 --> 00:31:40.288
- took a whole stash house down.
- You said to leave you out of it.

545
00:31:40.465 --> 00:31:43.298
This is not about credit. Hannah.
This is about doing the right thing.

546
00:31:43.868 --> 00:31:45.859
The right thing
would've been to kick it upstairs.

547
00:31:46.037 --> 00:31:49.871
- Let Hanford take it from there.
- Right. Go after bigger fish.

548
00:31:50.041 --> 00:31:51.702
So. why didn't you?

549
00:31:51.876 --> 00:31:53.810
You and I know if I turned
this over to Hanford.

550
00:31:53.978 --> 00:31:55.275
I would've ended up a footnote.

551
00:31:55.446 --> 00:31:57.277
If it did lead to bigger fish.
not even that.

552
00:31:57.448 --> 00:32:00.440
- But you don't know that.
- I do. Because I'm a cop. I've seen it.

553
00:32:00.618 --> 00:32:01.949
I know how it works.

554
00:32:02.787 --> 00:32:05.756
- And I'm not a cop. right?
- It's just different for me.

555
00:32:05.924 --> 00:32:08.654
Sergeant's exam is coming up.
I get extra points for commendations.

556
00:32:08.826 --> 00:32:11.420
I thought you were doing this
to help the people on your beat.

557
00:32:11.596 --> 00:32:13.621
Or is that something
you thought I wanted to hear?

558
00:32:13.798 --> 00:32:16.892
I did help them.
I got some bad guys off the street.

559
00:32:17.068 --> 00:32:18.558
Just not as many as you could have.

560
00:32:20.505 --> 00:32:23.906
You helped me when I needed help.
I won't forget it.

561
00:32:32.717 --> 00:32:34.275
Hey. I just ran into
Marcus downstairs.

562
00:32:34.452 --> 00:32:36.943
He told me about Collin Eisely.
Sounds like it didn't go well.

563
00:32:37.121 --> 00:32:40.784
I'm no less convinced of his connection
to Garrison Boyd's murder.

564
00:32:40.959 --> 00:32:44.861
You know. because of his history.
Mr. Eisely's money is in a blind trust.

565
00:32:45.029 --> 00:32:46.360
That means he can't touch it?

566
00:32:46.531 --> 00:32:49.625
More than that.
he can't even know how it's managed.

567
00:32:49.801 --> 00:32:52.793
Now. Eisely's trust is handled
by Robiskie Investments.

568
00:32:52.971 --> 00:32:55.633
a second-tier brokerage house
at best.

569
00:32:55.807 --> 00:32:58.275
I suspect more prominent firms
refused his business

570
00:32:58.443 --> 00:33:00.434
because of the miasma
that still surrounds him.

571
00:33:00.611 --> 00:33:03.808
His investments
are all in computer-traded funds.

572
00:33:03.982 --> 00:33:07.611
which deliver a return far less
than the profits he once made.

573
00:33:07.785 --> 00:33:10.049
- That's got to burn.
- Indeed.

574
00:33:10.254 --> 00:33:12.654
A man who had spent his entire life
exploiting weaknesses

575
00:33:12.824 --> 00:33:16.191
in the financial system would surely
chafe at such restrictions.

576
00:33:16.361 --> 00:33:18.989
So you thought he wanted to tap
into Ruby in order to profit off

577
00:33:19.163 --> 00:33:21.154
the information.
but there's no way he can profit.

578
00:33:21.332 --> 00:33:22.594
Or that I've found thus far.

579
00:33:22.767 --> 00:33:25.133
But I'm confident
that when TARU deliver its report.

580
00:33:25.303 --> 00:33:28.329
that mystery box is gonna connect
Eisely to the crime.

581
00:33:28.506 --> 00:33:32.067
In the meantime. I found this.

582
00:33:34.045 --> 00:33:36.343
A decade ago. when
Western companies were pillaging

583
00:33:36.514 --> 00:33:39.381
Iraq's resources in the name
of reconstruction.

584
00:33:39.550 --> 00:33:42.542
Eisely toured the oil fields
near Kirkuk.

585
00:33:42.720 --> 00:33:45.587
- That's Nadim Al-Haj.
- Al-Haj was his driver.

586
00:33:45.790 --> 00:33:48.691
He subsequently sponsored
his immigration into the U.S.

587
00:33:48.860 --> 00:33:51.988
Now. "lived in his building"
could be written off to chance.

588
00:33:52.163 --> 00:33:53.391
This cannot.

589
00:33:53.564 --> 00:33:57.022
Hey. a senior technician from TARU
is on his way up.

590
00:33:57.201 --> 00:33:59.328
Says he's got some news.

591
00:34:01.205 --> 00:34:02.934
Parts of it were pretty badly fused.

592
00:34:03.107 --> 00:34:06.008
but we were able to forensically
reconstruct most of the circuitry.

593
00:34:06.177 --> 00:34:07.542
And?

594
00:34:07.712 --> 00:34:10.943
It doesn't look like it was meant
to transmit anything anywhere.

595
00:34:11.616 --> 00:34:13.846
- So. what was it supposed to do?
- That's the thing.

596
00:34:14.018 --> 00:34:17.044
It doesn't store anything.
It doesn't re-route anything.

597
00:34:17.221 --> 00:34:19.553
It doesn't change anything.
It's just a maze of circuits.

598
00:34:19.724 --> 00:34:23.387
Data goes in one end
and comes out the other. That's it.

599
00:34:23.561 --> 00:34:26.029
So someone went to all the trouble
of digging a tunnel.

600
00:34:26.197 --> 00:34:29.030
exposing a transatlantic Internet cable
and murdering a guy

601
00:34:29.200 --> 00:34:32.966
- all so they could attach a devise that...
- Does absolutely nothing.

602
00:34:44.382 --> 00:34:46.247
I just got off the phone with Marcus.

603
00:34:46.417 --> 00:34:49.045
So far. Nadim Al-Haj has done
a pretty good job of disappearing.

604
00:34:49.220 --> 00:34:50.244
He's gone to ground.

605
00:34:50.421 --> 00:34:53.322
Knowing now he's not a hardened
terrorist. I imagine he's quite afraid.

606
00:34:53.491 --> 00:34:56.051
A murder and a flight
from the law were not part of his plan.

607
00:34:56.928 --> 00:34:59.396
- Mason?
- Hey.

608
00:35:00.131 --> 00:35:03.259
- I thought you were grounded.
- From the Internet.

609
00:35:03.434 --> 00:35:05.402
I mean. does this look
like the Internet to you?

610
00:35:06.804 --> 00:35:08.897
So. where New York's finest
nerds failed.

611
00:35:09.073 --> 00:35:12.008
- you're hoping yours will succeed?
- No offense to TARU.

612
00:35:12.176 --> 00:35:14.644
But the simple fact
is they must've missed something.

613
00:35:14.812 --> 00:35:17.110
Nadim Al-Haj did not dig
a 50-foot tunnel

614
00:35:17.281 --> 00:35:20.739
in order to install a plastic bauble with
as much function as a Christmas light.

615
00:35:20.918 --> 00:35:22.749
Until we find out what
the devise does.

616
00:35:22.920 --> 00:35:25.286
we cannot connect Collin Eisely
to any crime.

617
00:35:25.456 --> 00:35:27.754
So I've solicited a second opinion.

618
00:35:27.925 --> 00:35:29.825
It's my hope that Mason
will find something

619
00:35:29.994 --> 00:35:34.192
- that the police technicians missed.
- I'm trying. But don't hold your breath.

620
00:35:34.398 --> 00:35:36.366
I'm running parity bit tests.
file compares.

621
00:35:36.534 --> 00:35:39.298
metadata compares.
different character sets. packet sizes...

622
00:35:39.470 --> 00:35:42.200
You're running tests. We get it.

623
00:35:45.910 --> 00:35:48.435
I'm gonna get something to eat.

624
00:35:55.319 --> 00:35:59.016
Upstairs. may I presume that was
Hannah that you sent to voicemail?

625
00:35:59.190 --> 00:36:01.988
Yeah. I didn't think she was gonna
leave a message. but she did.

626
00:36:02.493 --> 00:36:04.620
Said she didn't feel great
about how we left things.

627
00:36:04.795 --> 00:36:05.887
and wanted to thank me.

628
00:36:06.063 --> 00:36:07.621
She didn't really come out
and say it.

629
00:36:07.798 --> 00:36:10.164
but I got the sense that what
she really wanted to know

630
00:36:10.334 --> 00:36:11.824
is what I'm gonna tell the captain.

631
00:36:12.470 --> 00:36:16.873
- What are you gonna tell him?
- I don't know. I mean...

632
00:36:17.341 --> 00:36:19.809
He's gonna wanna know
what happened. right?

633
00:36:20.211 --> 00:36:22.805
She's a police officer.
but she's also his daughter.

634
00:36:22.980 --> 00:36:24.948
Obviously the truth will disappoint.

635
00:36:28.986 --> 00:36:30.749
- I should tell him.
- You should not.

636
00:36:31.756 --> 00:36:34.224
You've expended enough time
and effort on Hannah Gregson.

637
00:36:34.392 --> 00:36:37.657
Telling him will only embroil
you further and benefit no one.

638
00:36:40.698 --> 00:36:43.826
Well. thanks for not actually saying
the words "I told you so."

639
00:36:44.001 --> 00:36:46.492
Well. for the record. I thought she
was a subpar investigator.

640
00:36:46.671 --> 00:36:48.571
I'd no idea she was so cunning.

641
00:36:48.739 --> 00:36:51.003
Anyway. I sent Mason home
for the night.

642
00:36:51.175 --> 00:36:55.737
Thus far. his tests uphold
the dignity of the N.Y.P.D.

643
00:36:55.913 --> 00:36:59.371
The stream of zeroes and ones
generated by his tests

644
00:36:59.550 --> 00:37:02.542
entered one end of the device
and emerged a consistent

645
00:37:02.720 --> 00:37:05.086
formula seconds later. unchanged.

646
00:37:05.256 --> 00:37:10.250
It is quite literally a box
that does nothing.

647
00:37:13.864 --> 00:37:17.027
- Unless that's the whole point.
- What?

648
00:37:17.201 --> 00:37:20.898
The four milliseconds
that doing nothing would take.

649
00:37:27.211 --> 00:37:29.543
What difference would
four milliseconds make to anything?

650
00:37:29.714 --> 00:37:31.306
In your world and mine. none at all.

651
00:37:31.515 --> 00:37:33.983
To a human being.
it's a imperceptible amount of time.

652
00:37:34.151 --> 00:37:37.587
But the lion's share of trading
on Wall Street happens automatically.

653
00:37:37.755 --> 00:37:38.847
via computers.

654
00:37:39.023 --> 00:37:43.790
And in their world. milliseconds
translate to millions of dollars.

655
00:37:43.961 --> 00:37:47.294
Ruby is the fastest transatlantic cable
that there is.

656
00:37:47.465 --> 00:37:50.127
Terminates on American soil
at 60 Hudson Street.

657
00:37:50.301 --> 00:37:52.929
where. in order to extract
financial data first.

658
00:37:53.104 --> 00:37:56.267
the top investment firms
pay a premium to house their servers.

659
00:37:56.440 --> 00:37:58.499
Now. any company
which does not lease a space

660
00:37:58.676 --> 00:38:00.735
at 60 Hudson
is at instant disadvantage.

661
00:38:01.846 --> 00:38:04.406
Would you care to guess
which firm is not flush

662
00:38:04.582 --> 00:38:07.813
with enough capital to earn
a spot at 60 Hudson?

663
00:38:10.855 --> 00:38:14.484
Robiskie Investments.
They manage your blind trust.

664
00:38:14.659 --> 00:38:16.854
Only their servers
are in a different building.

665
00:38:17.061 --> 00:38:19.825
Their data comes in from
a slower transatlantic cable.

666
00:38:19.997 --> 00:38:22.192
One that is usually
two milliseconds behind.

667
00:38:22.366 --> 00:38:25.961
A market closes halfway around the
world. currency drops. a regime falls.

668
00:38:26.137 --> 00:38:28.970
the news hurdles across the globe
at the speed of light.

669
00:38:29.140 --> 00:38:32.166
The larger firms' computers
buy and sell thousands of shares

670
00:38:32.343 --> 00:38:35.107
before the one that holds
your money even gets the news.

671
00:38:35.279 --> 00:38:39.841
So you planned to turn the tables.
Slow Ruby down by four milliseconds.

672
00:38:40.017 --> 00:38:42.952
Suddenly the big firms
are the ones at a disadvantage.

673
00:38:43.120 --> 00:38:45.213
Your blind trust
would start making more money.

674
00:38:45.389 --> 00:38:47.050
And your hands would stay clean.

675
00:38:47.224 --> 00:38:50.523
Other firms and clients would benefit
too. anyone who pulled their data

676
00:38:50.695 --> 00:38:52.162
from a source other than Ruby.

677
00:38:52.330 --> 00:38:54.560
But for a man pathologically driven
to play the game.

678
00:38:54.732 --> 00:38:58.532
that's a small price to pay.
Might even be a plus.

679
00:38:58.703 --> 00:39:01.331
Given that it would hide
your gains amongst the crowd.

680
00:39:03.674 --> 00:39:07.735
You give me a lot of credit.
Like I said before. it's a brilliant plan.

681
00:39:07.912 --> 00:39:12.576
But even if you're right.
you still have a problem.

682
00:39:12.750 --> 00:39:14.377
You can't link me to any of it.

683
00:39:15.820 --> 00:39:18.254
Well. when my colleagues
and I got together this morning.

684
00:39:18.422 --> 00:39:20.014
I said the same thing.

685
00:39:20.191 --> 00:39:22.853
I also asked about something
that's been bugging me.

686
00:39:23.027 --> 00:39:26.758
When you first hired Nadim Al-Haj.
the job didn't include murder.

687
00:39:27.398 --> 00:39:29.992
Once he killed Garrison Boyd.
you must've promised him

688
00:39:30.167 --> 00:39:31.896
a pretty big payday to keep him quiet.

689
00:39:32.069 --> 00:39:34.867
Especially with him going on
the run for who knows how long.

690
00:39:35.039 --> 00:39:39.339
But with your finances watched
so closely. how could you pay him?

691
00:39:39.510 --> 00:39:42.206
When I crossed paths
with Mr. Al-Haj the other day.

692
00:39:42.380 --> 00:39:45.713
he absconded with a poster tube.
a conspicuous detail in itself.

693
00:39:45.883 --> 00:39:49.614
given that he was so busy destroying
so much other evidence.

694
00:39:49.787 --> 00:39:52.756
I thought perhaps he'd retained
a keepsake. some schematics.

695
00:39:52.923 --> 00:39:55.517
some leverage to hold over you
should the need arise.

696
00:39:55.693 --> 00:39:57.684
But when Detective Bell raised
his question.

697
00:39:57.862 --> 00:40:01.696
I remembered noticing something
when we were here yesterday.

698
00:40:02.900 --> 00:40:06.267
That's not the same painting
that was here the first time we visited.

699
00:40:06.437 --> 00:40:09.065
It was a Picasso.
<i>Woman's Portrait.</i>

700
00:40:09.240 --> 00:40:10.730
Not well-known.

701
00:40:10.908 --> 00:40:14.867
but even a lesser work
by the master must be worth millions.

702
00:40:15.546 --> 00:40:16.638
Is it here?

703
00:40:16.814 --> 00:40:18.645
We've already reported it stolen.

704
00:40:18.816 --> 00:40:21.114
No dealer is gonna touch it.

705
00:40:21.285 --> 00:40:23.810
Al-Haj won't be able to get a dime.

706
00:40:25.189 --> 00:40:27.316
You tell us if we're wrong. Mr. Eisely.

707
00:40:27.758 --> 00:40:29.953
But we don't get the sense
he's a professional killer.

708
00:40:30.127 --> 00:40:32.220
It's only a matter of time
before we find him.

709
00:40:32.396 --> 00:40:34.159
And given that his
payday's going away.

710
00:40:34.331 --> 00:40:37.061
it's a good bet
that when we do. he'll talk.

711
00:40:38.936 --> 00:40:40.460
Now. you like to make deals. right?

712
00:40:40.704 --> 00:40:44.800
How about before we find him.
you make one right now?

713
00:40:49.246 --> 00:40:51.077
Oh. Joan?

714
00:40:52.316 --> 00:40:54.910
- Hi.
- Nice work today.

715
00:40:55.085 --> 00:40:57.485
- On the Eisely thing.
- Oh. thanks.

716
00:40:57.655 --> 00:41:00.988
- I'll pass that on to Sherlock.
- I'm sorry.

717
00:41:03.360 --> 00:41:04.622
For what?

718
00:41:12.937 --> 00:41:14.529
She told you?

719
00:41:14.772 --> 00:41:17.536
You just seemed a little off
these last couple of days.

720
00:41:17.741 --> 00:41:20.141
I know it wasn't the credit.

721
00:41:20.311 --> 00:41:23.610
You and Holmes don't care
about that stuff. but...

722
00:41:25.616 --> 00:41:27.948
- Whatever it was...
- You know what? She just got excited.

723
00:41:28.118 --> 00:41:29.608
That's all.

724
00:41:29.787 --> 00:41:32.017
I don't think you should help her
again.

725
00:41:33.691 --> 00:41:36.319
She is what she is.

726
00:41:36.694 --> 00:41:42.291
She wants what she wants.
I love her but I love this job too.

727
00:41:42.466 --> 00:41:43.797
The people who do it...

728
00:41:47.538 --> 00:41:49.403
She's gotta do better.

729
00:41:52.676 --> 00:41:54.507
All right. good night.

730
00:41:57.500 --> 00:42:05.500
